#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.177"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.177:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.177:0.2"
msgid "18. Sañcetaniyavagga"
msgstr "18. Intention"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.177:0.3"
msgid "177. Rāhulasutta"
msgstr "177. With Rāhula"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.177:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ "
"bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.177:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu yā ca bāhirā pathavīdhātu, "
"pathavīdhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"“Rāhula, the interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just "
"the earth element."

msgctxt "an4.177:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "an4.177:2.3"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindati, "
"pathavīdhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the earth element, "
"detaching the mind from the earth element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.165"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.177:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu yā ca bāhirā āpodhātu, āpodhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water "
"element."

msgctxt "an4.177:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "an4.177:3.3"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā āpodhātuyā nibbindati, āpodhātuyā "
"cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the water element, "
"detaching the mind from the water element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.177:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu yā ca bāhirā tejodhātu, tejodhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire "
"element."

msgctxt "an4.177:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "an4.177:4.3"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā tejodhātuyā nibbindati, tejodhātuyā "
"cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the fire element, "
"detaching the mind from the fire element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.177:5.1"
msgid ""
"Yā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu yā ca bāhirā vāyodhātu, vāyodhāturevesā."
msgstr ""
"The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air "
"element."

msgctxt "an4.177:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘Taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti, evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This should be truly seen with proper understanding like this: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "an4.177:5.3"
msgid ""
"Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā vāyodhātuyā nibbindati, vāyodhātuyā "
"cittaṃ virājeti."
msgstr ""
"When you really see with proper understanding, you reject the air element, "
"detaching the mind from the air element."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.177:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, rāhula, bhikkhu imāsu catūsu dhātūsu nevattānaṃ na attaniyaṃ "
"samanupassati, ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, bhikkhu acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi "
"saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees these four elements as neither self nor belonging to "
"self, they’re called a mendicant who has cut off craving, untied the "
"fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit has made an end of suffering.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.177:6.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
